This paper is about termination analysis of logic programs, which is a topic in programming languages and logic (PL) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the use of trees, which is a common data structure in algorithms and data structures (DS). Finally, the paper proposes a dynamic approach to termination analysis, which is related to software engineering (SE) and could potentially be applied to other areas of computer science.
